<h2 id="how-to-run-the-vaahstore" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#how-to-run-the-vaahstore" aria-hidden="true">#</a> How to run the VaahStore</h2>
<h3 id="step-1-install-vaahstore" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#step-1-install-vaahstore" aria-hidden="true">#</a> Step 1. Install VaahStore</h3>
<p>To install Vaahstore go into <code v-pre>VaahCMS &gt; Extends &gt; Modules</code> click on <code v-pre>install</code> button on top right corner.</p>
<p>Then a <code v-pre>Install Modules</code> sidebar will open, inside that search <code v-pre>Store</code> and click on <code v-pre>Install</code> button.</p>
<h3 id="step-2-activate-store" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#step-2-activate-store" aria-hidden="true">#</a> Step 2. Activate Store</h3>
<p>After installation a new module of <code v-pre>Ecommerce for VaahCMS</code> will added inside <code v-pre>VaahCMS &gt; Extends &gt; Modules</code>, click on <code v-pre>Activate</code> button.</p>
<h3 id="step-3-add-sample-data" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#step-3-add-sample-data" aria-hidden="true">#</a> Step 3. Add sample data</h3>
<p>To add sample data click on <code v-pre>Import Sample Data</code> of <code v-pre>Ecommerce for VaahCMS</code> module.</p>
